[Date / Cases / Deaths
26 Jun 2017 / 190 / 10
15 Sep 2017 / 319 / 14
6 Oct 2017 / 376 / 14
13 Oct 2017 / 397 / 15
20 Oct 2017 / 431 / 17
27 Oct 2017 / 457 / 18

In the last week 26 more cases are reported with 1 more death. More than a 1/3 of the cases had neither homelessness nor substance abuse risk factors. It is possible that subclinical hepatitis A in food handlers may be responsible for some of the cases with no clear risk factors. Mandating hepatitis A vaccination among food handlers, as done in San Diego County, should be a consideration in Michigan. - Mod.LL

The state of Michigan can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5413115,225. A county map can be seen at http://geology.com/county-map/michigan-county-map.gif. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
